ocuments.\n   - You might want to check the “Guidance and Best Practices” section.\n\n3. **Check for AI/ML Specific Requirements:**\n   - FedRAMP has specific requirements for continuous monitoring. Look for any mention of AI/ML model drift within the continuous monitoring requirements.\n   - You can also search within the documents for terms like \"AI\", \"ML\", \"model drift\", and \"continuous monitoring\".\n\n4. **Consult with Experts:**\n   - If you are still unable to find clear information, consider consulting with FedRAMP experts or professionals who specialize in FedRAMP compliance.\n\n5. **Review Industry Publications:**\n   - Look for articles or white papers from reputable sources that discuss FedRAMP requirements in the context of AI/ML.\n\n### Example Search Query:\nWhen on the FedRAMP website, you can use the search function to look for terms like:\n- \"continuous monitoring AI\"\n- \"FedRAMP AI/ML requirements\"\n\n### Additional Resources:\n- **NIST Publications:**\n  - The National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) often provides frameworks that FedRAMP is based on. Look for NIST SP 800-53 and related revisions.\n  \n- **FedRAMP Community Forums:**\n  - Sometimes, community forums or discussion boards can provide insights from other organizations that have gone through the FedRAMP process.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to gather authoritative information to verify the claim regarding FedRAMP requirements for AI/ML model drift monitoring.","status":"completed","startTime":1771624491060,"endTime":1771624556271,"duration":65211,"timestamp":"2026-02-20T21:55:56.271Z"},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_017oU1xGsW9bQ4pb8srrj3vr","name":"synth_synthesize","tool":"synth_synthesize","toolName":"synth_synthesize","serverId":"synth","serverName":"synth","executedOn":"synth-sandbox","arguments":{"agents":[{"role":"data_extraction","task":"Search for 'FedRAMP AI ML authorization 2025 2026' and 'NIST AI Risk Management Framework FedRAMP' and 'FedRAM